Korea's Building of Powerful Nation Supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- Ibrahim S. Shema, deputy national chairman of the People's Democratic Party of Nigeria and head of its delegation that visited the DPRK, said that he was deeply moved to see the Korean people dynamically advancing to build a great prosperous powerful nation, rallied close around leader Kim Jong Il.
 Visiting different places of Korea he pointed out that they could witness achievements in Korea and the firm will of the Korean people to build a more prosperous country, single-mindedly united around their leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea's reunification will surely be achieved as it is led by Kim Jong Il, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is energetically working to bring a reunified and prosperous country to posterity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The People's Democratic Party, the government and the people of Nigeria positively support the Korean people in their efforts to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We pay noble respects to the heroic Korean people working hard to build a great prosperous powerful nation under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea will display its might as a great prosperous powerful nation in the near future.
 We will make positive efforts to develop the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation in the future, too.

Famous Work on Movement of Koreans in Japan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- Today marks the lapse of 11 years since leader Kim Jong Il sent the historic letter "On Developing the Movement of Koreans in Japan on to a New High Stage" to the officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans residing in Japan on the 40th anniversary of the formation of Chongryon.
 Rodong Sinmun today dedicates an article to this anniversary, which says the historic letter serves as a highly important guideline reliably guaranteeing a bright future of the movement of Koreans in Japan as it clearly indicates the main orientation of the work of Chongryon, the basic mission of the movement of Koreans in Japan and the principal task which Chongryon should uphold as its fighting program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the letter fully displayed its judiciousness and vitality over the last 10 odd years in the course of the development of the movement, the author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under so grim situation, Chongryon has not collapsed but risen up like a giant, has not sagged but gathered strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is not an inch of deflection in the unbounded patriotic loyalty, warm love of the homeland and noble national conscience cherished by the Koreans in Japan who think that they can never fall like dead leaves, betraying their leader and motherland embracing, defending and taking care of them buffeted by raging storms in an alien land. Their faith and will are unshaken. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongryon should preserve the exploits of President Kim Il Sung, the founder of Chongryon and the sun for the destiny of the Koreans in Japan, and intensify its work as taught by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Chongryon officials and Koreans in Japan should revere Kim Jong Il with a single mind and remain boundlessly loyal to his leadership, true to the behests of the President. And they should wage a more vigorous struggle for achieving the independent reunification of the country with concerted efforts of our nation under the banner of the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration together with the people in the north and the south.

Russian Chorus Performs in Hamhung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hamhung, May 23 (KCNA) -- The Russian State Academic People's Chorus Named after M. E. Pyatnichki gave performances at the Hamhung Grand Theatre in South Hamgyong Province on May 22 and 23.
 The chorus which had come here carrying with it the warm friendly feelings of the Russian people towards the Korean people staged colorful numbers including choruses, instrumental music and dances spiced with strong national flavor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
ï¿½@The performers truthfully represented the Russian people's life and feelings with deep emotion and beautiful rhythms in chorus and dance "In the Glass City," dance "Mixed Dance of Vologda," choruses "Flying over Mountains and Hills," "Oh, Thick Fog," "Oh, Vast Land of Siberia" and "Oh, That Unforgettable Night". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian artistes also successfully presented female solo and chorus "Swan in Reed Field," male chorus "Hey, Farmers," female chorus "My Husband on Field" and instrumental music "Music of Saratov Folk Song" and other pieces with high artistry and peculiar skills, deeply impressing the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their performances were acclaimed by the audiences for vividly representing ardent patriotism, national sentiment and optimistic life of the Russians.

RS on Failure of U.S. in "Human Rights Diplomacy" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- Forty-seven countries including a number of non-aligned and developing countries were elected member nations of the newly inaugurated UN Human Rights Council at a recent UN General Assembly session. Commenting on this, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says:
 Thus the United States and other countries of the West tasted a bitter cup of failure in their "human rights diplomacy" though they sought to make the Council a theatre of their solo performance in a bid to interfere in the domestic affairs of the progressive countries and put pressure upon them under the false cloak of "defense of human rights". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., styling itself an "international human rights judge", laid obstacles in the process of the foundation of the UN Human Rights Council, coming out with unreasonable argument only to fail even to have a finger in its election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a proper judgment passed by the international community on the U.S. outrageous human rights abuses, "spread of U.S.-style democracy" and the reactionary and preposterous nature of its "human rights" policy. The U.S. dared not poke its nose into the election. This proved once again that it is very afraid of strong denunciation and fair judgment of its human rights crimes by the international community.
 The U.S. imperialists have used the human rights issues as a means of overthrowing the governments and systems of other countries. This is a downright challenge to the trend of global independence and a mockery of international justice and human conscience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world cannot be stable and the human rights issues cannot see a fair solution without holding at bay the U.S. imperialists' maneuvers to use the "human rights issues" as a means of interference in the internal affairs of other countries and nations and infringement upon their sovereignty, shelving their own brutal human rights abuses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the UN Human Rights Council has been founded to deal with international human rights issues, it cannot fulfill its mission as an international organization with impartiality as its principle, if the politicization of human rights issues and double standards, especially the attempts to interfere in the internal affairs of other countries under the pretext of these issues are allowed again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To defend international justice and human rights, all the countries and nations should resolutely frustrate the criminal moves of the U.S. and other countries of the West to trample other countries underfoot with the "human rights stick", seeking the politicization of human rights and double standards

RS Rebuts Bush's Theory of "Third World War" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- The sophism about "theory of the third world war" recently made by U.S. President Bush is nothing but a revelation of a dangerous scenario to escalate the U.S. "anti-terrorism war" for aggression worldwide in the future. 
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. It goes on:
 The "anti-terrorism war" started by the United States with the "September 11 incident" as a momentum was, in essence, a reckless use of strength to put the anti-imperialist independent countries under control and realize its ambition for world domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. escalation of the "anti-terrorism war" is throwing the world into confusion and disorder while bringing unspeakable misfortune and disasters to peoples.
 The Afghan and Iraqi wars were typical examples disclosing the reactionary, aggressive and criminal nature of the "anti-terrorism war" being waged by the U.S. imperialists. As the world community comments, their aggression brought these countries not freedom and democracy but a vicious cycle of socio-political confusion, disorder, terrorism and revenge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only fear of terrorism and uneasiness prevail in the world as it is sunken deep into a whirlpool of a vicious cycle of terrorism, revenge, destruction and death due to the U.S. "anti-terrorism war." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fear of terrorism is the nightmare that has haunted the international community since the U.S. start of the "anti-terrorism war." What is clear is that this war is the root cause of this worldwide instability and fear of terrorism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the U.S. imperialists seek to steadily escalate the war. 
 Bush's "theory of the third world war" is a manifestation of the U.S. dangerous intention to use even nuclear weapons without hesitation in a bid to carry out its strategy for world domination.  The reactionary nature and potential danger of Bush's theory lie in that his forces seek to put the world under their control by use of nukes. 
 With nothing can the U.S. imperialists ever cover up the criminal nature of their "anti-terrorism war" and shirk the responsibility for having driven the world to a vicious cycle of terrorism and revenge, the article concludes.

Folk Amusement Customs of Korean People in May
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- The sagacious and civilized Korean nation has enjoyed many folk amusements peculiar to each month from ancient time. 
 They used to play various folk games in May, the season of fresh verdure.
 Lantern play was famous in the Pyongyang area in the period of Koryo dynasty. It kicked off when darkness set in. Spectacular was the lantern amusement on the cross-roads in front of the Taedong Gate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the playing, two poles are planted and linked with a string on their tops. After tying various animal-shaped lanterns to the string, peoples loosen and tighten the string, enchanting spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a play with cushion-candles. Pyongyangites make round straw cushions with candles set in the center and float hundreds of cushion-candles on the River Taedong.
 In this season, Korean women used to dye finger nails red with touch-me-not flower. They mashed petals of flowers along with alum or salt and put it on nails and wrapped them with bean or castor beam leaves. The practice, which shows the emotional feelings and tender heart of the Korean women, originated in the period of the Koryo dynasty and is done among women even today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rope jumping to the tune of songs is popular among girls. Such amusement can be seen in anywhere of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scene of children's rope jumping of the mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang," the grand monumental masterpiece of the 21st century, stroke Korean and foreign viewers with admiration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are various amusements for children to cultivate their judgment, collectivism and physical strength. Among them are children's play of hitting a short wooden stick and horse riding with a stick.
